sentences: Mark "Vinnie" Dombroski (born December 4, 1962) is an American musician, best known as the lead vocalist and main songwriter for the American rock band Sponge.
Vinnie Dombroski was born on December 4, 1962 in Detroit, Michigan.
Sponge released their ninth studio album, Lavatorium, on August 6, 2021.
Give The Orbitsuns What They Want (2012)
South Detroit Honky Tonks and Other UFOs (2018)
